    "The reference wave field is an average wave field from different intact samples.",
    "We trained each encoder network with five models and took the median value of their metrics.",
    "We have discovered that training with reference wavefields significantly improves the models employing different encoder networks.",
    "Moreover, more advanced encoder networks, such as 1D-DenseNet, appear to benefit more from this approach.",
    "Figure 10 illustrates the accuracies of the models trained with normalized dataset over different crack sizes."
